entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how did you feel in that moment

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: panicked cause i really wanted to make him not hate me and i mostly failed

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that sounds really hard

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: hard on him i mostly mostly got by with a couple of scrapes on my ego

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay tell me about a situation that you wish you had handled differently

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: when when that all went down i tried to to talk to him but i got distracted for the very first time that day and so instead of having my verbal gloves up i managed to take a whole bunch of words to the side of the head and fall over a trash can it was not my most graceful moment

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: oh what is something you feel guilty about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i feel guilty about lots of stuff i feel guilty about eating more often than anything else

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: cause i really love junk food it is really good i have very little food willpower cause i used to be a fat guy

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: laughter tell me about the hardest decision you have ever had to make

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am not sure what the hardest decision i ever had to make was made a lot of hard decisions i guess it was pretty hard to leave los angeles after my ex and my best friend did a whole bunch of nasty stuff but it was not even that hard cause it pushed me to do it so it is a tricky question madam

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what made you decide to do that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh you know broken collarbone severe pain get surgery on it it all seemed like it made sense at the time

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well there is the part where she is intensely physically beautiful there is the part where she manages to hit me with the best inspiration words there is the part where she actually works on the exact things that make me excited there is the part where she pops in and out of my life at the exact right instance and then there is the part where she is a hundred percent kind and caring all the time all of those things are really nice but then when you add to that and compound it with the fact that she does this all without wanting anything in return i do not know that is smitten

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how do you know them

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: what a funny question how do i know them as though she is multiple people how did you know i know her through my bicycle friends

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: cool how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: the hard part is going to bed but as soon as i get to to sleepland i am pretty much there until an earthquake hits so i i get to sleep poorly but then i am a pro at it so it does not matter

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: less verbose and that is about it my dark circles get slightly larger and i am pretty much the exact same dude because i have been doing it most of my life

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: so stoked that i might as well be on fire

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: because the universe in its infinite i suppose the word is sardonic sense of hor has managed to convince me of the reality of magic in the arthur c clark sense so as a fortunate and vaguely aware being eh it is my privilege to get to enjoy more time like this

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah my excitement is increasing at an almost exponential rate and i am feeling more and more inspired all the time if i could just work on the motivation i would be set

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: not since you asked me on the form a little while ago no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no i used to think i had it but who knows at this point that was awhile ago

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you tell me about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i was very unhappy with most of my life for a very long time and then i moved to los angeles and started having fun and then that is yeah the rest is ancient history

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: twenty thirteen working on my shoes this morning was really nice doodling an art project that all my friends helped and put on that is that was really nice it is a nice feeling

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: awesome how would your best friend describe you

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: that is a very good question i am not actually sure i will ask him later today though
